{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "For drugs with a single target, such as dimetacrine, pefloxacin, ropivacaine, and apremilast, both GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 demonstrated good predictive performance, achieving 100% prediction accuracy (Fig. 4 and Supplementary data 4).",
    "However, for drugs with two or more targets, except for dezocine, both GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 could not accurately predict all the targets of the drugs.Aligning LLMs with Humans: A Survey of ChatGPT in Pharmacology For example, irbesartan, widely used to treat hypertensive patients with type 2 diabetes, relieves hypertension and reduces blood sugar levels.",
    "It has direct targets, including AGTR1 (Angiotensin II receptor type 1) and JUN (Jun proto-oncogene, AP-1 transcription factor subunit).",
    "However, GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 only recorded AGTR1 as the target for irbesartan, omitting JUN (refer to Fig. 4).",
    "Similar issues were observed in the query tasks for silodosin, dequalinium, camostat, and other drugs (Fig. 4)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}